What is the hostname of the target system?
good, we will use this command to know the host name of the target system: 
hostname ----> the answer will be : wade7363

What is the Linux kernel version of the target system?
as we know there is a command who is responsible for that like -->
uname -a ----> the answer will be 3.13.0-24-generic

What Linux is this?
we can know this answer by followinf this path : etc/os-release
$ cat /etc/os-release
NAME="Ubuntu"
VERSION="14.04, Trusty Tahr"
ID=ubuntu
ID_LIKE=debian
PRETTY_NAME="Ubuntu 14.04 LTS" ------> this is what we need : Ubuntu 14.04 LTS
VERSION_ID="14.04"
HOME_URL="http://www.ubuntu.com/"
SUPPORT_URL="http://help.ubuntu.com/"
BUG_REPORT_URL="http://bugs.launchpad.net/ubuntu/"

What version of the Python language is installed on the system?
alright then that is easy one, we will use this command to know the version of the python language that installed on the system:
python --version     ----> Python 2.7.6

What vulnerability seem to affect the kernel of the target system? (Enter a CVE number)?
good, we will use google to search on that one, we will write this: 3.13.0-24-generic exploit, by the way you have to enhance your research skills :)
so the vulnerability CVE number is ----> CVE-2015-1328

